  "texts": [
    "6.3), this may be because people invest more in independent thinking in the process of deliberation with AI and realize the problematic aspects of AI's perspective.",
    "6.1.3 Appropriateness of Reliance.",
    "We further measured the appropriateness of participants' reliance on AI's suggestion by underreliance and over-reliance (Figure 7 (b)).",
    "Results show that there is no significant difference between Deliberative AI (𝑀=0.32, 𝑆𝐷=0.28) and XAI (𝑀=0.29, 𝑆𝐷=0.30) in terms of under-reliance.",
    "While significantly less over-reliance was observed in Deliberative AI (𝑀=0.47, 𝑆𝐷=0.31) than in XAI (𝑀=0.65, 𝑆𝐷=0.33, 𝑝 <0.001), which means that participants had more appropriate reliance on AI when collaborating with our proposed Deliberative AI."
  ]
}